title: Coroner identifies teen in northeast Vegas shooting
content:
LAS VEGAS (FOX5) -
Medical examiners released the identity of a teenager who died after being found shot Sunday in a northeast Las Vegas Valley neighborhood.
Del'Vonte Jenkins, 14, of Las Vegas, died from a gunshot wound to the chest. The Clark County Coroner's Office ruled his death a result of a homicide.
Las Vegas Metro police said officers were called to the 3600 block of Elegant Saint Court, near Pecos and Gowan roads, at about 7 p.m. on reports of a male shot.
The victim was rushed to University Medical Center Trauma, where he was later pronounced dead.
Citing an initial investigation, police said there was a gathering of friends and family members in the area at the time of the shooting. There were no arrests immediately made as a result.
Police urged anyone with information on the incident to contact Metro's Homicide Section at 702-828-3521 or Crime Stoppers at 702-385-5555.
Police said the incident marked the 124th homicide investigated by Metro this year.
